text: Pattazhy Vadakkekara is a village in Kollam district, Kerala, India. It is separated from Pattazhi by the Kallada River. ==Demographics== India census, Pattazhy Vadakkekara had a population of 14775 with 7020 males and 7755 females. ==References== Category:Villages in Kollam district
title: Pattazhy Vadakkekkara
